                                        <p>
                                            <ol>
                                                <li>Using Green's theorem, evaluate 
                                                $$\int_C \left\lbrack  \left(  x^2 + 10xy + y^2 \right) \ dx + \left(  5x^2 + 5xy \right) \ dy \right\rbrack$$
                                                where $C$ is the square with the vertices $\left(  0, 0 \right), \left(  2, 0 \right), \left(  0, 2 \right),$ and $\left( 2, 2  \right)$, oriented counter-clockwise.</li>
